# Server Conventions

## Module System

This is an ESM project (`"type": "module"` in package.json). All imports use ESM syntax.
**tsx watch** runs the dev server — it auto-restarts on file changes.

## Prisma Client (CRITICAL)

The Prisma client in `server/src/exports/prisma.ts` uses **lazy initialization** via a Proxy.
This is required because ESM evaluates all imports before any code in `index.ts` runs,
and `DATABASE_URL` isn't available until `dotenv.config()` executes.

```typescript
// CORRECT — always import from exports/prisma.ts
import { prisma } from '../exports/prisma';

// WRONG — never create a new PrismaClient elsewhere
import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';
const p = new PrismaClient(); // BREAKS — no adapter, no connection string
```

## Route / Controller Pattern

```
routes/<name>.routes.ts   → Express Router, defines HTTP methods + paths
controllers/<name>.controller.ts → Handler functions, imports prisma, returns JSON
```

All API routes are prefixed with `/api/`. Mount new routers in `index.ts`:
```typescript
app.use('/api/<name>', nameRoutes);
```

## Error Handling in Controllers

```typescript
// Standard pattern — always catch and return structured error
try {
  const data = await prisma.model.findMany({ ... });
  return res.status(200).json({ success: true, data });
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Context-specific message:', error);
  return res.status(500).json({ error: 'User-facing message' });
}
```

## Adding New Prisma Models

1. Edit `server/prisma/schema.prisma`
2. Run `npx prisma migrate dev --name <description>` from `server/`
3. Prisma client auto-regenerates — the lazy proxy picks up new models automatically

## Key Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.ts` | Express app, CORS, route mounting, Telegram polling |
| `exports/prisma.ts` | Singleton PrismaClient (Neon adapter, lazy) |
| `core/ai/intentParser.ts` | AI intent pipeline (Groq + tool calling) |
| `core/ai/prompts.ts` | System prompt for the AI engine |
| `core/engine/runner.ts` | Server-side workflow executor (send_payment, etc.) |
| `controllers/webhook.controller.ts` | Telegram update handler (largest controller) |
